{
  "doc_id": "prion_0557",
  "text": "An autopsy case of Creutzfeld-Jacob disease with widespread amyloid plaques is reported.\nA 45-year-old Japanese man, whose father had died of a similar disease, had a 5-year illness characterized by progressive cerebellar signs.\nMental changes and brain-stem signs developed in the late stage.\nMyoclonus frequently occurred.\nAkinetic mutism ensued.\nThe autopsy revealed spongiform encephalopathy with widespread amyloid plaques and extensive degeneration of the white matter.\nThis disease, Western Gerstmann-Sträussler-Scheinker disease and panencephalopathic type of Creutzfeld-Jacob disease are discussed.",
